  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out (acceptable at MRL 2). The operating envelope and applicability constraint are declared as structured inline objects with concrete numerical bounds. Validation coverage is honest about sparse sampling at envelope extremes.",
