    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "CPB hemolysis CFD operating envelope",
      "description": "The model is applicable within the following bounded operating conditions: blood flow rate 1.0–7.0 L/min (five discrete operating points: 1.0, 2.5, 4.0, 5.5, 7.0 L/min); impeller rotational speed 1500–3500 RPM (three nominal speeds: 1500, 2500, 3500 RPM); inlet hematocrit 35–45%; blood temperature 35–38 °C; pump inlet pressure 5–20 mmHg. Geometric tolerance envelope: impeller tip clearance 0.10–0.50 mm, volute gap width ±0.15 mm of nominal. Extrapolation beyond these bounds is not supported by the validation evidence base.",
      "lowerFlowRateLperMin": 1.0,
      "upperFlowRateLperMin": 7.0,
      "lowerSpeedRPM": 1500,
      "upperSpeedRPM": 3500,
      "lowerHematocritPct": 35,
      "upperHematocritPct": 45,
      "tipClearanceRangeMm": "0.10–0.50",
      "voluteGapToleranceMm": 0.15
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "CPB hemolysis model applicability constraint",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model is applicable only to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry family with impeller diameter 50–60 mm and volute design consistent with the reference geometry. The model is scoped to Newtonian blood rheology approximation valid at shear rates above 100 s⁻¹. It is not applicable to pulsatile flow regimes, axial-flow pump geometries, or operating points outside the declared flow-rate and speed envelope. Device must be a Class II CPB pump with predicate hemolysis data available for relative comparison (RH index method)."
    }
  },
