    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded with concrete numerical limits (flow rate 1.0–7.0 L/min, speed 1500–3500 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%, geometric tolerances). Validation coverage spans the envelope interior at five operating points; the low-flow/low-speed corner gap is acknowledged and bounded by conservative uncertainty extrapolation documented in the UQ records. The six scoped-out factors are appropriately excluded per MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device. The CFD model demonstrates adequate credibility to support the regulatory decision to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions, with the relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed for the baseline geometry. No credibility gaps remain unaddressed. The assessment team accepts the model for the declared COU within the stated operating envelope bounds.",
